Rating: 4
This is excellent. I make it once a week for the family. Whenever a recipe calls for butter and it is to be cooked at high heat I use ghee or clarified butter which does not have the same health concerns as butter at high temps. My changes are only to simplify the process. Cook the pork as directed. Remove from pan when done. Cook onion and rosemary on the stove top in the pork roasting pan. The onion releases enough moisture to de-glaze pan. When softened, add the cranberry sauce and the vinegar. Cut the pork and plate. Pour the released juices into the sauce, season with salt and pepper, spoon over pork and serve.

