I have made this several times for my boyfriend and myself and each time I make it I have made an adjustment. I have found that making the sauce separately and then cooking the pork right before I'm ready to serve it gives the sauce time to thicken up. Before adding the chicken broth I mix about one tablespoon of flour to it and then add it into the onion and rosemary. I also use about 1/2 to 2/3 cup of cranberry sauce this gives it more flavor. I cut the rosemary back to about 2 teaspoons so it doesn't over-power the cranberry. Serve with baked sweet potatoes and asparagus! Excellent!

