Just a quick note to the reviewer from Nantucket - pork is commonly served medium-rare now. Trich is pretty much a thing of the past, when sanitary conditions and healthy animals weren't regulated as much. Go into most any fine restaurant and you'll find pork served a lot more rare than it used to be. It does take some getting used to, but read up - you'll see that it's ok.

