Rating: 4
To capture more flavor in the sauce, I use the same pan to brown and roast the meat and to make the sauce. After the meat is cooked, I remove it from the pan and keep it warm. I cook the onions, rosemary, etc. in the drippings, before deglazing with the broth and then adding the cranberries and vinegar. It takes a few extra minutes but adds a dimension of flavor and saves the washing up of one pot.

