Rating: 3
Usually I am very disappointed in the epicurious recipes people rave over, but this one was actually good. The pork did take longer (abt. 20 min) to cook, even after searing and at that temp. I used shallots instead of onions and 1 clove of garlic in the sauce for a little more flavor; I omitted the rosemary as I'm not crazy about it. There is really plenty of sauce here for the amount of pork specified in the recipe--I made the mistake of doubling the sauce and we had a ridiculously huge amount of it. So, don't double it unless you double the meat; also don't add more cranberries or the sauce will be too tart. It's really almost perfect as-is. I served this with sugar snap peas and mashed new potatoes. While not quite elegant enough for company, I would make this again for quick but nice dinners at home for my family.

