Rating: 3
The speed and ease of preparation makes this recipe appealing. Even novice cooks can make this suitable-for-company dish. Make sure you really SEAR the tenderloin with high heat - try to get a crust. The 10 minute cooking time may seem short, but I bet the recipe assumes you are using meat not straight from the fridge, but meat that has been sitting out at room temperature for 30-60 minutes (this is actually a good, common technique). But do cook the meat until the internal temperature reaches 155 degrees. The sauce is a wonderful accompaniment. Sweet onions and shallots are acceptable alternatives to yellow onions, but you need to use the whole-cranberry canned sauce, if only for texture.

