I think one could safely use less cranberry sauce. Also, using two skillets is not necessary if you brown the pork in the same one you use to make the sauce, then transfer the pork to a roasting dish. As for the accompaniaments, I can do without suggestions such as this! I mean, come on: butternut squash and corn muffins? Boiled green beans with orange zest? Ice cream with warm chestnut sauce? This is just annoying and patronizing; it seems to be trying to turn a quick and easy recipe into an all-day marathon.

